 |YKOAt level 100, your level display is replaced by
 a renown label on the who list. Your heroism
 reputation determines whether you appear as
 [HERO], [ADV], or [VILN]. Heroism is changed by
 notable actions in the world, not by guild membership
 alone.

 Several advantages are given to those who
 reach this level band. Along with the prestige
 of renown, players may change their title at will
 with the |YKB'ltitle' |YKOcommand (unlocked earlier,
 at CHAMPION, level 50).

 In addition, level 100+ players have the option of adding
 a second guild, broadening their skills and
 overall scope. This second guild is governed
 by a variety of restrictions which are outlined
 in the dualguilds help file.

 See |YKBhelp mechanics reputation|YKO for more about how
 deeds can affect your public renown.
 Use |YKBreputation|YKO to see the broad shape of how the world
 speaks of you.
